title: Bug 6322: All types dialog shows obfuscated classes
description: The JDK 1.4 includes obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) that are being displayed prominently in the Open Type dialog.
OB: The obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) are prominently displayed in the Open Type dialog.
EB: The obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d) should be displayed with less prominence in the Open Type dialog.
SR: To reproduce the issue, open the Open Type dialog and observe the prominence of the obfuscated classes (a, a1, b, c, d).
